Desert Warrior  x2<br />
Desert Spearman  x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Free Peoples<br />
I bid 3-4 in hopes of going first and starting at The Riddermark. I included 3 Aragorns incase I dont go first. I chose The Ruling Ring over ATAR &#39;cause I dont have much Burden Removal.I try to wound minions as much as I can BEFORE the skimish phase with cards like Defend it and Hope and Quick as May Be. Then take advantage of the elves strength against wounded minions.<br />
<br />
Shadow<br />
The Southron half is mainly based around wounding before the skirmish.  The Sauron side is a basic Sauron condition side. The Moria Archer Troop and Archer Commander are there mainly because I wanted more archery power.<br />
<br />
Now when I get some EOF cards (which I currently have none of) I will modify this deck drasticly. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
